# Clarify before assume

All agents (plan mode, agent mode, subagents): **do not guess** product behavior, UX, scope, or implementation choices. **Ask first** when prompt unclear or proposed work adds unstated logic.

## When to ask (mandatory)

- Prompt unclear, contradictory, or missing acceptance criteria
- Plan or code path would add behavior, UX, scope, or technical approach user did not describe
- Multiple valid implementations; user did not choose
- Before **`CreatePlan`** or substantive implementation: list unstated decisions; if any remain → **`AskQuestion`** (plain ask if tool unavailable)

## Not an assumption (no re-ask)

- Repo rules, skills, mandatory structure ([yagni.mdc](yagni.mdc) guardrails)
- Patterns already established in touched code — match surrounding file
- User explicitly delegated ("your choice", "use best judgment")

## Planning mode

- Do **not** ship plan with silent "we will assume X" bullets
- Ask first, or mark open decisions **blocked pending user answer** — stop before implementation steps
- Plan file location/metadata: [plan-documents.mdc](plan-documents.mdc)
- Every plan body (`.cursor/plans/*`, CreatePlan output) must start with an **Uncertainty gate** section per [plan-documents.mdc](plan-documents.mdc)

## How to ask

- **1–2** critical questions per turn
- Prefer **`AskQuestion`** when choices enumerable
- State what repo rules already fix vs what is still unknown

## Example triggers

| Situation | Ask |
| --- | --- |
| "Add export button" — format/location/menu unspecified | Yes |
| "Fix sidebar bug" — no repro steps | Yes |
| New dialog — user didn't say modal vs floating window | Yes |
| New feature module — use **`functions/`** + **`*_manager.ts`** | No (repo law) |
| Run dev scoped gate after edits | No (repo law — [dev-scoped-verify.mdc](dev-scoped-verify.mdc)) |
| Run full **`yarn testbatch:verify`** before commit | No (repo law) |

